Privacy Policy
RoFlow Chrome Extension · Last updated: June 2026
1. Overview

RoFlow is a Chrome extension. We take your privacy seriously. This policy explains what data the Extension accesses, how it is used, and where it is stored.

2. Data we collect

RoFlow collects and stores the following data locally in your browser using Chrome's storage API:

Your Roblox username and user ID (if you choose to link your account)
OAuth access and refresh tokens from Roblox (stored locally, never sent to our servers)
Your watchlist and alert preferences
Cached market data from Rolimons
Extension settings

We do not operate any backend server. No data is transmitted to or stored on any server we control.

3. Data we do not collect
Your Roblox password — we use OAuth, no password is ever accessed
Browsing history
Personal information beyond your Roblox public profile
Payment or Robux balance information
Any analytics or telemetry data
4. Third-party API requests

When you use RoFlow, your browser makes requests directly to:

Rolimons (rolimons.com) — for market data and price history
Roblox (roblox.com and its subdomains) — for user info, inventory, and trade data

These requests are made from your browser directly. Your IP address and request data are subject to Rolimons' and Roblox's own privacy policies.

5. Permissions used
storage — to save your settings, watchlist, and cached data locally
identity — to launch the Roblox OAuth login flow via Chrome's identity API
alarms — to periodically refresh market data in the background
notifications — to alert you to price spikes or new projected items (only if enabled)
tabs — to open external links (Rolimons, Roblox catalog) in new tabs
6. Data retention and deletion

All data is stored locally in your browser. You can delete all RoFlow data at any time by removing the Extension from Chrome, or by clearing the Extension's storage via Chrome's developer tools. Uninstalling the Extension removes all locally stored data.

7. Children's privacy

RoFlow is not directed at children under 13. We do not knowingly collect any information from children under 13. If you believe a child has used the Extension in a way that raises privacy concerns, please contact us.

8. Changes to this policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will update the "Last updated" date at the top of this page when we do. Continued use of the Extension after changes constitutes acceptance of the revised policy.

